<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1170" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1170">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/63.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                        d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d1170fn1">Transmitted
                                    by the Department December 16 to the Red Cross and the Mayor of
                                    El Paso.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-15">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1913</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>This morning the Spanish Minister at this capital called to ask me to
                                have the various authorities at El Paso, Texas, thanked for their
                                kindness to Spanish refugees at that place.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>